The Federal Government of Nigeria through the Ministry of Youth and Sports Development has condemned in clear terms a fictitious story  that a British kit company had to come to the rescue of Nigeria contingents at the ongoing Commonwealth Games in Birmingham. An online platform claimed  a British sportswear manufacturer had to answer an SOS call from the Nigerian contingent  after they were left without kits.   Preseason: Jesus hits hattrrick as Arsenal hammer Sevilla…     PHOTOS: Tobi Amusan, Sports Minister meet in UK     Okonkwo joins Alexandra from Arsenal   According to the statement, Gino Rufinato, manager of the MG Sportswear firm, which is based in a town near host city Birmingham, at first thought it was a “wind-up” before launching his 14 staff into action. While reacting to the said release, a media aide to the sports minister, Toyin Ibitoye, said it was most unfortunate that such a malicious lies has been going around.